com.fasterxml.cachemate
Interface CacheElement<K,V>

All Known Subinterfaces:
TwoKeyCacheElement<K1,K2,V>
All Known Implementing Classes:
POJOCacheElement, TwoKeyPOJOCacheElement
public interface CacheElement<K,V>

Interface for "simple" cache elements that map a single _key to a value. Serves as the base for multi-_key variants, as well as for concrete single-_key implementations.

Author:
Tatu Saloranta

Method Detail

putEntry

CacheEntry<K,V> putEntry(long currentTime,
                         K key,
                         V value,
                         int weight)
Method for putting specified entry in this cache; if an entry with the key exists, it will be replaced. Note that time-to-live used is the default TTL.

Parameters:
currentTime - Logical timestamp of point when this operation occurs; usually system time, but may be different for tests. Typically same for all parts of a single logical transaction (multi-level lookup or removal)
key - Key of the entry to insert
value - Value for the entry to insert
weight - Combined weights of key and value, not including overhead of entry wrapper
Returns:
Previous value for the key, if any; usually null but could be non-null for race condition cases
